topic.title: GPIO Adapter Setting Block

body.p: The GPIO Adapter block defines GPIO pin sources. The On-Chip GPIO adapter defined in the first instance is mandatory, must always be the first adapter instance, and must be the only adapter of this type.

Any additional GPIO Adapters define peripheral bus-connected GPIO. These adapter types are optional and start from the second instance. Some examples include TWI-based GPIO expanders and SGPIO stream.

p.ph: Other adapter types may be defined in future firmware releases.Need to decide whether we want to discuss futures in a customer document like this. It seems to be an important point that the list of supported connections will grow.

entry.p: GPIO Adapter Type - The first instance will always be MM On-Chip GPIO
Associated On-chip Input Interrupt GPIO Pin
GPIO Adapter Type - for SGPIO slot

note.p: The maximum supported GPIO pin number is 512, and the maximum MAX7311/PCA9555-Compatible GPIO expander number is 32.
